From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ArcBoost Builder <build@arcboost.local>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:07:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 01/13] ArcBoost: add CircularBin to BinType enum
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First patch in the ArcBoost series. Adds the new bin-type tag without yet
wiring up any logic that consumes it; subsequent patches add BinMapper
support, the histogram split-finder, dispatch, config plumbing, and the
Python API kwarg.

The enum value is appended (CircularBin = 2) rather than inserted so that
existing serialized datasets and saved models — which round-trip the
numeric BinType through model.txt — remain readable.
---
 include/LightGBM/bin.h | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/LightGBM/bin.h b/include/LightGBM/bin.h
index 5826f238..141f14ca 100644
--- a/include/LightGBM/bin.h
+++ b/include/LightGBM/bin.h
@@ -21,7 +21,12 @@ namespace LightGBM {
 
 enum BinType {
   NumericalBin,
-  CategoricalBin
+  CategoricalBin,
+  // ArcBoost: features whose domain is a circle (e.g. wind direction, hour of day).
+  // Splits are arcs `[a, b] mod period` rather than linear thresholds. The bin
+  // index is computed by modular arithmetic in BinMapper::ValueToBin (no binary
+  // search), and split-finding scans cyclic prefix sums of (g, h) histograms.
+  CircularBin
 };
 
 enum MissingType {
